        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:57PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northeast of Crestone Peak, or 42 miles west of Pueblo. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Silver Cliff and Rosita.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
